  "prompt": "Which is a suitable solar panel installation provider in La Habra, California CA?",
  "response": "When looking for a suitable solar panel installation provider in La Habra, California, it's important to consider factors such as reputation, experience, customer reviews, and pricing. Here are a few well-regarded solar companies that operate in the La Habra area:\n\n1. **SunPower by Sea Bright Solar**:\n   - **Website**: [seabrightsolar.com](https://www.seabrightsolar.com/)\n   - **Why Choose Them**: SunPower is known for its high-efficiency solar panels and comprehensive warranty. Sea Bright Solar is a certified SunPower installer with a strong reputation in Southern California.\n\n2. **SolarTech**:\n   - **Website**: [solartechonline.com](https://www.solartechonline.com/)\n   - **Why Choose Them**: SolarTech has been installing solar systems for over 20 years and is well-regarded for their customer service and quality of installation.\n\n3. **Verengo Solar**:\n   - **Website**: [verengosolar.com](https://www.verengosolar.com/)\n   - **Why Choose Them**: Verengo Solar has a strong presence in California and is known for its competitive pricing and financing options.\n\n4. **Titan Solar Power**:\n   - **Website**: [titansolarpower.com](https://www.titansolarpower.com/)\n   - **Why Choose Them**: Titan Solar Power offers a comprehensive service from consultation to installation and is praised for its customer service and aftercare.\n\n5. **Freedom Forever**:\n   - **Website**: [freedomforever.com](https://www.freedomforever.com/)\n   - **Why Choose Them**: Freedom Forever is known for its quality installations and offers a 25-year warranty on both panels and labor, which is a significant advantage.\n\nBefore making a decision, it's advisable to:\n- **Request Quotes**: Get detailed quotes from at least three providers to compare pricing and services.\n- **Check Reviews**: Look at customer reviews on sites like Yelp, Google, and the Better Business Bureau.\n- **Verify Credentials**: Ensure the company is licensed, insured, and has good standing with industry organizations like the Solar Energy Industries Association (SEIA).\n\nBy doing your due diligence, you can find a reliable and cost-effective solar panel installation provider in La Habra.",
